  Plotly.js Simple Subplot</a> by fuzzy (<a href="https://codepen.io/fkE3">@fkE3</a>)
  on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.</span>
</p>
<script async src="https://static.codepen.io/assets/embed/ei.js"></script>

**Details**
I have a scatter plot with a shape background with `"layer": "below"` on version `1.53.0`. When upgrading the plot to version `1.54.0`, hover labels stops working. 

**How to reproduce**

Example: https://jsfiddle.net/jorgebg/2g0mb6tz/6/

1. Hover the data point of the center of the plot. The label doesn'tshow up. Hover labels of the data points on the sides work though.
2. Change the plotly.js version to `1.53.0` (line 5).
3. Hover the data point in the center of the plot and check the label shows up.

Code used in the example:

```
    const data = [{
        "x": ["2020-04-18T10:00:00.000Z", "2020-04-18T11:00:00.000Z", "2020-04-18T12:00:00.000Z", ],
        "y": [2.68, 2.42, 2.45],
        "type": "scatter",
      }];

      const shapes = [{
        "fillcolor": "#79bc6a",
        "layer": "below",
        "line": {
          "width": 0
        },
        "opacity": 0.2,
        "type": "rect",
        "x0": "2020-04-18T10:00:00.000Z",
        "x1": "2020-04-18T12:00:00.000Z",
        "xref": "x",
        "y0": 0,
        "y1": 15,
        "yref": "y"
      }];

      Plotly.newPlot("plot", data, {
        shapes: shapes,
      });
```

I checked the [release notes](https://github.com/plotly/plotly.js/releases) and I couldn't find any changes on the shapes API, I think this is a bug. Please let me know if you need more details. Thank you!
